pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Chemical-resistant gloves made of barrier laminate, butyl rubber ≥14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥14 mils, neoprene rubber ≥14 mils, polyvinyl chloride (PVC) ≥14 mils, or Viton® ≥14 mils; Shoes plus socks

Active_Ingredients.name: Thiamethoxam
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Group 4A insecticide (neonicotinoid class, nicotinic acetylcholine receptor agonist)

Active_Ingredients.name: Mefenoxam
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Group 4 fungicide (phenylamide class, interferes with fungal RNA synthesis)

Active_Ingredients.name: Thiabendazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Group 1 fungicide (methyl-benzimidazole carbamate class, disrupts ß-tubulin assembly)

Active_Ingredients.name: Fludioxonil
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Group 12 fungicide (phenylpyrrole class, interferes with MAP/histidine protein kinase)

Active_Ingredients.name: Sedaxane
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Group 7 fungicide (succinate dehydrogenase inhibitor, carboxamide class)

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling, and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco, or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice; Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow; Do not induce vomiting unless told to by a poison control center or doctor; Do not give anything to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor or going for treatment.

Application_Info.max_product_per_acre_per_season: 0.083 lb thiamethoxam, 0.004 lb fludioxonil and 0.013 lb mefenoxam per acre per calendar year
